FBIS3-13377 "drnes049_n_94005" FBIS-NES-94-049 Document Type:Daily Report 14 Mar 1994 LEBANON Ja'ja' Followers Suspected in Terrorist Activities Army Maintains Roadblocks NC1203131994 (Clandestine) Radio Free Lebanon in Arabic 1145 GMT 12 Mar 94 NC1203131994 (Clandestine) Radio Free Lebanon Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Text] For the third day running, the Lebanese Army continues to man fixed and mobile roadblocks at the entrances to the Lebanese Forces command and the home of Dr. Samir Ja'ja' in Ghidras. Lebanese Army personnel continue to search all travelers to Ghidras without exception, including journalists, who are being prevented from bringing in their recording equipment and cameras. [passage omitted]
